description: This source file implements the basic functions for the Slap Owo Uoao Object, including creation, removal, object enrollment, and initialization routines within a service logic component. It is part of the Service Logic Aggregation Plane (SLAP) for Cisco's RDK platform, primarily defining object lifecycle and setup functions.

methods.name: ANSC_HANDLE SlapOwoUoaoCreate(ANSC_HANDLE hContainerContext,ANSC_HANDLE hOwnerContext,ANSC_HANDLE hAnscReserved)
methods.description: Constructs a new Slap Owo Uoao Object, allocates memory for it, initializes base object attributes including name, handles, OID, and function pointers, and calls enrollment and initialization routines.

methods.name: ANSC_STATUS SlapOwoUoaoRemove(ANSC_HANDLE hThisObject)
methods.description: Destroys the object by calling the SlapOwoRemove function on the object instance.

methods.name: ANSC_STATUS SlapOwoUoaoEnrollObjects(ANSC_HANDLE hThisObject)
methods.description: Enrolls the necessary objects required by this object by invoking the SlapOwoEnrollObjects function.

methods.name: ANSC_STATUS SlapOwoUoaoInitialize(ANSC_HANDLE hThisObject)
methods.description: Initializes the object, including setting its OID, function pointers, and specific object type, after first calling the base initialization routine.
